    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-09T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-09T21:00:00-05:00" n="853"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d853">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.6363/169: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-10T11:00:00+09:00"
                            >January 10, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 10—12:11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Embassy’s 1, January 4, 5 p.m., American oil interests in Japan.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The conversations between the special representatives of the American and
                        British oil interests and the Japanese officials commenced yesterday at the
                        Tokyo Club in order to avoid premature publicity in a pleasant and
                        conciliatory atmosphere. The first day was devoted principally to
                        generalities, the Japanese doing most of the talking. Conversations will be
                        resumed this afternoon.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>No Embassy officials are attending meetings but the oil interests will
                        keep the Embassies fully informed. Important developments will be conveyed
                        to the Department by telegraph and memoranda of the conversations by
                        mail.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
